### English Title:
The Military Advisor to the Presidential Leadership Council in Yemen Discusses U.S. Strikes Against Houthis

### English Text Summary:
Lieutenant General Mohammed Al-Maqdeshi, military advisor to the Presidential Leadership Council in Yemen, stated that U.S. strikes against the Houthis have achieved multiple objectives, including the destruction of weapons and the killing of several Houthi leaders. He expressed skepticism about reports of an imminent military operation by the legitimate government against the Houthis, emphasizing that military arrangements are typically made secretly. Al-Maqdeshi believes that the Houthis will ultimately be defeated, whether through regional or U.S. support, and criticized the Houthis for causing suffering among Yemenis while exploiting the Palestinian cause. He acknowledged having information about potential arms smuggling from Oman to the Houthis but denied having evidence to confirm it. The article also mentions an upcoming program that will address various questions regarding the situation.

